         <abstract>
            <p>We examine a cell-vertex finite volume method which is applied to a model parabolic convection-diffusion problem. By using techniques from finite element analysis, local errors away from all layers are obtained in a seminorm that is related to, but weaker than, the L&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; norm.</p>
          </abstract>
